# Changelog

## 0.1.0

### Added
- Initial bash-only Gemini terminal client
- Interactive Ctrl+D chat loop
- Config file support through ~/.config/gemini-cli/config
- API key support from environment or config
- Model cache support
- --update-models command
- --models command
- --select-model command
- --test-model command
- --attach FILE support
- Rolling conversation context
- Human-readable session logs
- Context snapshots in session logs
- Project Lead startup notice
- Startup message-window explanation line
- Optional jq support for stronger JSON parsing
- Best-effort awk/sed fallback parsing when jq is unavailable
- Text-like attachment support
- Binary/media inlineData attempt through base64
- Credits command
- Config set/unset commands

### Notes
- This edition avoids Python by design.
- This edition is not intended to be a curl example; it is an end-user terminal chat client with lighter dependencies.
- JSON handling is inherently less robust than bash/python3 or ncurses/python unless jq is installed.
